## astronomical.json.tmpl for the New Belchertown WeeWX skin
##
## Generates real astronomical data as JSON for the BirchesWX sun/moon
## card, using the EXACT SAME computation as this skin's own almanac
## diagram (build_almanac_diagram_payload in user.new_belchertown) —
## not a separate or approximated calculation. That function already
## produces, per body (sun/moon): current alt/az, rise/transit/set
## epochs, a 24h track of (minute_of_day, altitude) samples every 30
## minutes, and a "transit-centering" x_offset that shifts the body's
## OWN track so its OWN daily peak (transit) sits at the middle of the
## diagram — which is what makes a single shared center line meaningful
## for both curves even though the sun and moon transit at different
## clock times. Earlier drafts of this file approximated all of this in
## JavaScript and never quite matched the skin's real diagram; this
## version hands the front-end the exact same sampled data instead.
##
## This deliberately does NOT use #errorCatcher Echo — an inline error
## string substituted into JSON output would break JSON parsing for
## every field after it. Every risky access is wrapped in its own
## #try/#except instead, falling back to Python None (rendered as JSON
## null) so one missing field can't take down the whole file.
