## ---- Moon phase name / fullness / age (same fields celestial.inc displays) ----
## ---- Moon's real visual tilt (bright-limb position angle, corrected for
## parallactic angle so it's relative to the observer's own zenith rather
## than the celestial pole) — genuine positional astronomy, not a
## stylistic constant. Two standard, independently-documented formulas:
##   chi = position angle of the bright limb's midpoint, measured from
##         the celestial north point, increasing through east
##         (Meeus, "Astronomical Algorithms" ch. 48)
##   q   = parallactic angle — converts chi from "relative to the
##         celestial pole" to "relative to the observer's zenith"
##         (standard spherical-astronomy formula; q is exactly 0 or 180
##         at the moment of meridian transit, which is how this was
##         sanity-checked)
## The result (chi - q) is the angle, measured from celestial north
## through east, at which the bright limb's midpoint sits AS SEEN BY
## THIS OBSERVER right now.
